  "text": "In order to determine how Kp-10 promotes breast cancer cell invasion, we employed the use of zymographic analysis of matrix metalloprotease secretion. We found that treatment of MDA-MB-231 cells that express endogenous GPR54 [CITATION_1] with either 10 or 100 nM of Kp-10 increases the secretion of MMP-9 (Fig. 2D) , revealing for the first time that Kp-10 signaling via GPR54 in breast cancer cells stimulates the secretion of MMP-9.",
